Crucially, never combine more than two items before using a tool. If you have an odd number of 'soft' items (e.g., 3 soft, 1 hard), combine one 'soft' item with the 'hard' item first and then frame it. This allows the remaining two 'soft' items to be combined and cut for higher value.

Crucially, do NOT combine an item that has been 'cut' with an item that has been 'framed'; this consistently leads to very low values. Aim to create one 'cut' item and one 'framed' item, then submit to secure a score of around 50. The initial hint about handling 3 cuttable items by pairing one with a non-cuttable item is useful for setting up these two distinct paths.
